        jTextArea1.setText("Clay soils feel very sticky and rolls like \nplasticine when wet. They can hold more\ntotal water than most other soil types and \nalthough only about half of this is available \nto plants, crops seldom suffer from drought.\nThey swell when wetted and shrink when \ndried, so a certain amount of restructuring \ncan take place in these soils depending on \nweather conditions.\nThey lie wet in winter and so stock should be \ntaken off the land to avoid poaching \n(the compaction of soils by animals hooves).\nThey are very late in warming up in the spring\nbecause water heats up more slowly than \nmineral matter. They are normally fairly rich\n in potash, but are deficient in phosphates.\nClay soils usually need large infrequent \ndressings of lime.");
